const MDXLayout = "wrapper"
export default function MDXContent({
  components,
  ...props
}) {
  return <MDXLayout {...layoutProps} {...props} components={components} mdxType="MDXLayout">

    <h2 {...{
      "id": "cis-kubernetes-benchmark-141---rancher-233---kubernetes-116"
    }}>{`CIS Kubernetes Benchmark 1.4.1 - Rancher 2.3.3 - Kubernetes 1.16`}</h2>
    <p><a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://releases.rancher.com/documents/security/2.3.x/Rancher_Benchmark_Assessment.pdf"
      }}>{`单击这里下载 PDF 版本的安全自测指南`}</a></p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "概述"
    }}>{`概述`}</h2>
    <p>{`本文档是对 Rancher v2.3.3 安全加固指南的补充。加固指南提供了用于加固 Rancher 的生产环境集群的指南，该基准自测指南旨在帮助您针对安全基准中的每个控制，来评估加固集群的安全级别。本指南将逐步介绍各种控制，并提供更新的示例命令以审核 Rancher 创建的集群中的合规性。此文档的适用人群是：Rancher 运维人员、安全团队、审核员和决策者。`}</p>
    <p>{`加固指南旨在与特定版本的安全加固指南，CIS Kubernetes Benchmark，Kubernetes 和 Rancher 一起使用：`}</p>
    <table>
      <thead parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="thead">
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`自测指南版本`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Rancher 版本`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`安全加固指南版本`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Kubernetes 版本`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`CIS Benchmark 版本`}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`自测指南 v2.3.3`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Rancher v2.3.3`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`安全加固指南 v2.3.3`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Kubernetes v1.16`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Benchmark v1.4.1`}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>{`由于 Rancher 和 RKE 以容器的方式安装 Kubernetes，因此 CIS Kubernetes Benchmark 中的许多控制验证检查均不适用，完成 CIS 扫描后，这些检测对应的结论是`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`Not Applicable`}</inlineCode>{`（不适用）。`}</p>
    <p>{`有关每个审核的更多详细信息，包括测试失败的原因和补救措施，您可以参考 CIS Kubernetes Benchmark v1.4.1 的相应部分。登录`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://www.cisecurity.org/benchmark/kubernetes/"
      }}>{`CISecurity.org`}</a>{`后，可以下载基准测试。`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "测试控制方法"
    }}>{`测试控制方法`}</h2>
    <p>{`Rancher 和 RKE 通过 Docker 容器安装 Kubernetes 服务。配置在初始化时通过给容器传递参数的方式设置，而不是通过配置文件定义。`}</p>
    <p>{`如果控制审核与原始 CIS 基准不同，则将提供 Rancher Labs 特定的审核命令以进行测试。执行测试时，您将需要访问所有三个 RKE 角色的主机上的 Docker 命令行。这些命令还利用了`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://stedolan.github.io/jq/"
      }}>{`jq`}</a>{`和`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl/"
      }}>{`kubectl`}</a>{`（使用有效的 kubeconfig 文件）来测试和评估测试结果。`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "已知的失败的计分测试"
    }}>{`已知的失败的计分测试`}</h2>
    <p>{`Rancher 目前无法通过以下计分测试，Rancher Labs 会通过发布版本升级来解决这些问题。`}</p>
    <ul>
      <li parentName="ul">{`1.1.21 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`--kubelet-certificate-authority`}</inlineCode>{` argument is set as appropriate (Scored)`}</li>
      <li parentName="ul">{`2.1.8 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`--hostname-override`}</inlineCode>{` argument is not set (Scored)`}</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "1---master-node-security-configuration"
    }}>{`1 - Master Node Security Configuration`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "11---api-server"
    }}>{`1.1 - API Server`}</h3>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "111---ensure-that-the---anonymous-auth-argument-is-set-to-false-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.1 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--anonymous-auth`}</inlineCode>{` argument is set to `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`false`}</inlineCode>{` (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--anonymous-auth=false").string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--anonymous-auth=false`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "112---ensure-that-the---basic-auth-file-argument-is-not-set-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.2 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--basic-auth-file`}</inlineCode>{` argument is not set (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--basic-auth-file=.*").string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`null`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "113---ensure-that-the---insecure-allow-any-token-argument-is-not-set-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.3 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--insecure-allow-any-token`}</inlineCode>{` argument is not set (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--insecure-allow-any-token").string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`null`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "114---ensure-that-the---kubelet-https-argument-is-set-to-true-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.4 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--kubelet-https`}</inlineCode>{` argument is set to `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`true`}</inlineCode>{` (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--kubelet-https=false").string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`null`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "115---ensure-that-the---insecure-bind-address-argument-is-not-set-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.5 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--insecure-bind-address`}</inlineCode>{` argument is not set (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Notes`}</strong></p>
    <p>{`Flag not set or `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--insecure-bind-address=127.0.0.1`}</inlineCode>{`. RKE sets this flag to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--insecure-bind-address=127.0.0.1`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--insecure-bind-address=(?:(?!127\\\\.0\\\\.0\\\\.1).)+")'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`null`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "116---ensure-that-the---insecure-port-argument-is-set-to-0-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.6 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--insecure-port argument`}</inlineCode>{` is set to `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`0`}</inlineCode>{` (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--insecure-port=0").string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--insecure-port=0`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "117---ensure-that-the---secure-port-argument-is-not-set-to-0-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.7 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--secure-port`}</inlineCode>{` argument is not set to `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`0`}</inlineCode>{` (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--secure-port=6443").string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--secure-port=6443`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "118---ensure-that-the---profiling-argument-is-set-to-false-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.8 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--profiling`}</inlineCode>{` argument is set to `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`false`}</inlineCode>{` (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--profiling=false").string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--profiling=false`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "119---ensure-that-the---repair-malformed-updates-argument-is-set-to-false-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.9 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--repair-malformed-updates`}</inlineCode>{` argument is set to `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`false`}</inlineCode>{` (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Note:`}</strong>{` This deprecated flag was removed in 1.14, so it cannot be set.`}</p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "1110---ensure-that-the-admission-control-plugin-alwaysadmit-is-not-set-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.10 - Ensure that the admission control plugin `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`AlwaysAdmit`}</inlineCode>{` is not set (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--enable-admission-plugins=.*(AlwaysAdmit).*").captures[].string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`null`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "1111---ensure-that-the-admission-control-plugin-alwayspullimages-is-set-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.11 - Ensure that the admission control plugin `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`AlwaysPullImages`}</inlineCode>{` is set (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--enable-admission-plugins=.*(AlwaysPullImages).*").captures[].string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`AlwaysPullImages`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "1112---ensure-that-the-admission-control-plugin-denyescalatingexec-is-set-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.12 - Ensure that the admission control plugin `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`DenyEscalatingExec`}</inlineCode>{` is set (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--enable-admission-plugins=.*(DenyEscalatingExec).*").captures[].string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`DenyEscalatingExec`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "1113---ensure-that-the-admission-control-plugin-securitycontextdeny-is-set-not-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.13 - Ensure that the admission control plugin `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`SecurityContextDeny`}</inlineCode>{` is set (Not Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Notes`}</strong></p>
    <p>{`This `}<strong parentName="p">{`SHOULD NOT`}</strong>{` be set if you are using a `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`PodSecurityPolicy`}</inlineCode>{` (PSP). From the CIS Benchmark document:`}</p>
    <blockquote>
      <p parentName="blockquote">{`This admission controller should only be used where Pod Security Policies cannot be used on the cluster, as it can interact poorly with certain Pod Security Policies`}</p>
    </blockquote>
    <p>{`Several system services (such as `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`nginx-ingress`}</inlineCode>{`) utilize `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`SecurityContext`}</inlineCode>{` to switch users and assign capabilities. These exceptions to the general principle of not allowing privilege or capabilities can be managed with PSP.`}</p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--enable-admission-plugins=.*(SecurityContextDeny).*").captures[].string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`null`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Document`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "1114---ensure-that-the-admission-control-plugin-namespacelifecycle-is-set-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.14 - Ensure that the admission control plugin `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`NamespaceLifecycle`}</inlineCode>{` is set (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--enable-admission-plugins=.*(NamespaceLifecycle).*").captures[].string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`NamespaceLifecycle`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "1115---ensure-that-the---audit-log-path-argument-is-set-as-appropriate-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.15 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--audit-log-path`}</inlineCode>{` argument is set as appropriate (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Notes`}</strong></p>
    <p>{`This path is the path inside of the container. It's combined with the RKE `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`cluster.yml`}</inlineCode>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`extra-binds:`}</inlineCode>{` option to map the audit log to the host filesystem.`}</p>
    <p>{`Audit logs should be collected and shipped off-system to guarantee their integrity.`}</p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Audit`}</strong></p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`docker inspect kube-apiserver | jq -e '.[0].Args[] | match("--audit-log-path=/var/log/kube-audit/audit-log.json").string'
`}</code></pre>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Returned Value:`}</strong>{` `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--audit-log-log=/var/log/kube-audit/audit-log.json`}</inlineCode></p>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Result:`}</strong>{` Pass`}</p>
    <h4 {...{
      "id": "1116---ensure-that-the---audit-log-maxage-argument-is-set-to-30-or-as-appropriate-scored"
    }}>{`1.1.16 - Ensure that the `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`--audit-log-maxage`}</inlineCode>{` argument is set to `}<inlineCode parentName="h4">{`30`}</inlineCode>{` or as appropriate (Scored)`}</h4>
    <p><strong parentName="p">{`Notes`}</strong></p>
    <p>{`Audit logs should be collected and shipped off-system to guarantee their integrity. Rancher Labs recommends setting this argument to a low value to prevent audit logs from filling the local disk.`}</p>
